---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | The Lawn Guide"
  description="Why The Lawn Guide exists, who's behind it, and how it's funded."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-600 font-medium mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-forest-900 leading-tight tracking-tight">
        A real lawn, a real gardener, no nonsense.
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8 font-serif italic">
        Most UK lawn content online is written by people who've never actually scarified a lawn in March or watched their grass turn yellow in a heatwave. The Lawn Guide is different.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm James, and I write everything you read here. I'm based in the UK, I have my own lawn that I've been renovating, and every product I review I've either used personally or tested specifically for the article. No drop-shipped reviews, no AI slop, no recycled press releases.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <p>
        Honest, practical guides to UK lawn care. Month-by-month seasonal advice tied to British weather, not American climates. Reviews of products you can actually buy from UK retailers. Step-by-step tutorials with photos from my own garden.
      </p>

      <h2>How it's funded</h2>
      <p>
        The Lawn Guide makes money through affiliate links. When you click a link to a retailer like Amazon, Crocus, or a UK lawn care specialist and make a purchase, I earn a small commission at no extra cost to you.
      </p>
      <p>
        This matters because it means I have an incentive to recommend things that actually work. A bad recommendation breaks trust, you don't come back, and the whole thing falls apart. So I only recommend products I'd genuinely use myself.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, feedback, or product to test? Email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>